      • toMap

        @SafeVarargs
public static <K,V,M extends java.util.Map<? super K,? super V>,T> M toMap(M dest,
                                                                                         T... keyValues)
        Puts all given key-values into dest map, and returns the dest map.

        The key-values is an array of which elements are in order of key followed by value, means the first element (index 0) is key, second (index 1) is value, third is key, fourth is value and so on. If the array miss the last value, the last value will be considered as null.

        Type Parameters:
        K - key type
        V - value type
        M - type of dest map
        T - type of element
        Parameters:
        dest - dest collection
        keyValues - given key-values
        Returns:
        dest map

      • getNested

        @Nullable
public static <T> T getNested(java.util.Map<?,T> map,
                                         T key,
                                         java.util.Set<T> stack)
        Nested get value from given map with given key. This method gets value of given key, then let the value as next key to find next value and keep looping. If last value as key cannot find next value, the last value will be returned. If given key cannot find at least one value, or a same value in the given stack (which will cause an infinite loop), return null.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of element
        Parameters:
        map - given map
        key - given key
        stack - stack to store the historical values
        Returns:
        nested value from given map with given key
